As the world marks 16 days of activism against gender-based violence, agencies working in Kakuma Refugee Camp and Kalobeye Resettlement Camp are holding acitivities to sesitise the host community on sexual abuse. While coordinating a ten kilometer community run themed creating safe spaces for women and the girl child, it was revealed that many women in refugee camps have been victims of gender based violence most of them experiencing the violence while on transit to the refugee camps and others while in the camp. 